Intent

Create a new implementation guide for adding a Devourment integration adapter to Full Bodied Animation, with the adapter translating Devourment swallow-related mod events into neutral internal Full Bodied triggers. The goal is to keep Devourment external, preserve Full Bodied as the animation/timeline engine, minimize churn to working systems, and leave a clean seam for future integrations such as Tasting Tamriel.

Constraints

Do not patch or modify Devourment core as the primary strategy.
Do not remove or replace the existing animation-graph event pipeline yet.
Do not force Devourment-specific assumptions deep into Full Bodied core systems.
Keep changes modular and easy to back out.
Prefer additive changes over refactors unless a small refactor clearly reduces long-term complexity.
The first supported case should be narrow: successful Devourment swallow, oral/stomach locus, humanoid predator and prey, non-endo.
Logging should be explicit and easy to grep, using a dedicated integration prefix.
Config should remain the source of truth for mapping external triggers to timeline/script keys.
Do not implement speculative support for Tasting Tamriel yet, but preserve a clean future seam for it.
Do not make unapproved architectural leaps beyond the scope of this assignment.

Scope

This assignment covers:

introducing a neutral internal external-trigger model
adding a Devourment integration module
plumbing a dedicated external-trigger queue into the update loop
adding config parsing for Devourment trigger mapping
starting a timeline from a normalized Devourment swallow trigger
building logging and checkpoints around the above

This assignment does not cover:

broad Devourment feature coverage
patching Devourment plugin records
restoring removed Devourment paired-idle architecture
adding Tasting Tamriel integration now
implementing every possible locus/endo/creature case in the first pass

